description:
In 1844, a group of believers turned to the Word of God and rediscovered the great truths and pillars of the faith: the sanctuary plan of salvation, the Second Advent movement, the Sabbath, the state of the dead, and the Spirit of Prophecy. Truth, long lost, was given back to the world. But Satan, fearing this message, began a counter theology, introducing false doctrine counterfeits. Dispensationalism, speaking in tongues, secret societies, spiritism, the Quakers, the Mormons, B’nai Brith, Jehovah’s Witnesses, and the ecumenical movement were also born in 1844. The message of the Three Angels of Revelation was to be buried under a quagmire of religious movements and doctrine designed to hide the spirit of truth from the minds of humanity.
